  - m_Id: 18106501590126631
    m_Localized: You don't have enough Holomoney
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18106501590126637
    m_Localized: For users who are playing HOLOSAGA for the first time..
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18106501590126638
    m_Localized: 'Holosaga is a defense game that anyone can easily enjoy!


      It
      has a simple controls, and it''s not that difficult to avoid monster''s patterns.


      Choose
      the unit you want and create your own unit combination to clear the stage!

'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18106501590126639
    m_Localized: About the units and the COLLECTION
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18106501590126640
    m_Localized: 'A unit of Hololive idols is a key player in the game.


      Units
      perform the patterns and damage monsters to prevent invasion (some units doesn''t
      have damage but has a supporting skills, though). You can make units even stronger
      through upgrades in stores.


      COLLECTION allows you to check the information
      about the units monsters you''ve gotten, and see how much you''ve collected
      them. That information can be obtained when you''ve gotten a unit or encountered
      a monster.'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18106501590126641
    m_Localized: About SHOP
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18106501590126642
    m_Localized: 'In SHOP, units can be purchased and upgraded using HOLOMONEY.


      Some
      units are open from the start, but if you have a locked unit, you will need
      to purchase it as HOLOMONEY. If you upgrade the unit, you will also be able
      to use new patterns that the unit could not use before.


      In the unit
      skin store, you can also purchase and use the unit''s skin. The applied skin
      is reflected in the in-game.'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18106501590126643
    m_Localized: About UNIT SELECT
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18106501590126644
    m_Localized: "When you start the game, you must first select the unit you want
      to use in the game. \n\nYou can choose up to four units, and any number less
      than that is possible. If you like challenges, trying to clear the game with
      fewer units than before can be a fun factor, too.\n\nThe icon's star marks
      lets you check the status of your unit's upgrade, and it is recommended that
      you select a unit with a higher upgrade value as much as possible."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18106501590126645
    m_Localized: About unit roles
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18106501590126646
    m_Localized: 'Each unit has a set role group, and it is recommended to set the
      initial arrangement according to the set role group. The role consists of three
      groups - Projectile, Range-Attacker, and Supporters. Each of the specialties
      is as follows.


      Projectile Unit - A unit that fires and attacks with
      a projectile. All projectile units possess a maximum range.

      Range-Attacker
      Unit - A unit that attacks ''all'' monsters in a set range.

      Supporter
      units - A units that have the ability to support units, instead of having no
      attack capability in the default pattern.


      Projectile units and supporter
      units have low HP on average, so it is recommended to place them in the rear,
      and Range-attacker units have a lot of HP and a narrow range, so it is recommended
      to place them in the front.'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18106501590126647
    m_Localized: About level-up
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18106501590126648
    m_Localized: "Defeating monsters gives you EXP, and when enough EXP points are
      gathered, you can level up the unit's POWER and HP by pressing the number keys.
      \n\nPOWER is a stat that makes the unit stronger, such as the attacking and
      healing ability of the unit.\n\nAs you level up, the unit becomes stronger,
      but the waiting time for death increases accordingly, so be careful."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18106501590126649
    m_Localized: About Switching
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18106501590126650
    m_Localized: 'Switching is a feature that allows you to move a unit to a different
      tile.


      You can activate switching by either clicking on the unit or
      pressing the designated keys (A, S, D, F). Once switching is active, click
      on the tile where you want to move the unit, and its position will change.


      Use
      switching to arrange your formation and dodge monster patterns!'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18106501590126651
    m_Localized: About Active Patterns
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18106501590126652
    m_Localized: 'Certain units have an ''active pattern'', which can be obtained
      through unit upgrades.


      An active pattern is a conceptual such as ''skill'',
      which is used by the user by pressing the key down or button directly. If the
      unit is able to use the active pattern, the icon of the active pattern appears
      in the top GUI.'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 19127775963615232
    m_Localized: The unit doesn't have enough unitExp.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 26492980561416192
    m_Localized: Would you like to buy this unit?
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 26742962652680192
    m_Localized: Projectile
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 26742962698817536
    m_Localized: Range-attacker
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 26742962707206144
    m_Localized: Supporter
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 34728367884832768
    m_Localized: 'A random box containing various items.


      You can obtain a
      random box with a certain probability when you defeat monsters, and the drop
      rate increases with difficulty.'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 34728367939358720
    m_Localized: 95% chance for a certain amount of Holomoney, 4% chance for a unit,
      1% chance for a skin
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
